<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1323,668,974]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
Newly recorded in New Brunswick. Members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[968,1112,828,854]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Melandryini">Melandryini</taxonomicName>
are xylophagous (Pollock 
<number box="[371,435,868,894]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" value="2002.0">2002</number>
). In Nova 
<collectingCountry box="[558,634,868,894]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Scotia</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[647,758,868,893]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Prothalpia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undata">
<emphasis box="[647,758,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">P. undata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found primarily in mature and old red spruce (
<taxonomicName box="[359,514,908,933]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubens">
<emphasis box="[359,514,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Picea rubens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) forests although occasionally also in deciduous forests. In Québec, it has been beaten from dead branches of 
<taxonomicName box="[751,922,948,973]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis box="[751,922,948,973]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Quercus rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (D. Pollock, unpublished data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
